        "endTime": 3.718,
        "duration": 3.718,
        "text": "In this powerful story, Yuna is a Korean adoptee."
      },
      {
        "startTime": 3.718,
        "endTime": 7.942,
        "duration": 4.224,
        "text": "She is adopted at four months old and grows up in America."
      },
      {
        "startTime": 7.942,
        "endTime": 11.51,
        "duration": 3.568,
        "text": "Yuna learns the Korean language and visits Korea."
      },
      {
        "startTime": 11.51,
        "endTime": 14.568,
        "duration": 3.058,
        "text": "She sees herself reflected in her culture."
      },
      {
        "startTime": 14.568,
        "endTime": 17.554,
        "duration": 2.986,
        "text": "Yuna climbs a mountain to find her roots."
      },
      {
        "startTime": 17.554,
        "endTime": 23.889,
        "duration": 6.335,
        "text": "This is an inspiring story about reconnecting with lost heritage and finding belonging."
      },
      {
        "startTime": 23.889,
        "endTime": 26.22,
        "duration": 2.33,
        "text": "Imagine you are four months old."
      },
      {
        "startTime": 26.22,
        "endTime": 29.934,
        "duration": 3.714,
        "text": "You are taken from the country where you were born."
      },
      {
        "startTime": 29.934,
        "endTime": 33.356,
        "duration": 3.423,
        "text": "You are flown across an ocean to a new country."
      },
      {
        "startTime": 33.356,
        "endTime": 37.07,
        "duration": 3.714,
        "text": "You grow up in a place where no one looks like you."
      },
      {
        "startTime": 37.07,
        "endTime": 40.638,
        "duration": 3.568,
        "text": "You forget the language your birth parents spoke."
      },
      {
        "startTime": 40.638,
        "endTime": 44.798,
        "duration": 4.159,
        "text": "You forget the food, the customs, the sounds of home."
      },
      {
        "startTime": 44.798,
        "endTime": 48.657,
        "duration": 3.859,
        "text": "You spend twenty-two years trying to be someone else."
      },
      {
        "startTime": 48.657,
        "endTime": 51.943,
        "duration": 3.286,
        "text": "But then, one day, you decide to go back."
      },
      {
        "startTime": 51.943,
        "endTime": 55.001,
        "duration": 3.058,
        "text": "You decide to learn the language you lost."
      },
      {
        "startTime": 55.001,
        "endTime": 59.807,
        "duration": 4.806,
        "text": "You decide to reconnect with the heritage that was taken from you."
      },
      {
        "startTime": 59.807,
        "endTime": 65.239,
        "duration": 5.432,
        "text": "This is the story of Yuna—a story of loss, longing, and reclamation."
      },
      {
        "startTime": 65.239,
        "endTime": 72.53,
        "duration": 7.291,
        "text": "Between 1950 and 2000, over 200,000 Korean children were adopted by families in other countries."
      },
      {
        "startTime": 72.53,
        "endTime": 78.137,
        "duration": 5.607,
        "text": "Many of these children grew up as the only Asian person in their communities."
      },
      {
        "startTime": 78.137,
        "endTime": 83.389,
        "duration": 5.252,
        "text": "They lost connection to their birth language, culture, and heritage."
      },
      {
        "startTime": 83.389,
        "endTime": 86.302,
        "duration": 2.913,
        "text": "This story takes place during that time."
